.CD "uud, uudecode \(en decode a binary file encoded with uue"
.SX "uud\fR [\fB\(enn\fR]\fR [\fB\(ens \fIsrcdir\fR] [\fB\(ent \fIdstdir/\fR] \fIfile"
.FL "\(enn" "Do not verify checksums"
.FL "\(ens" "Name of directory where \fI.uue\fR file is"
.FL "\(ent" "Name of directory where output goes"
.EX "uud file.uue " "Re-create the original file"
.EX "uud \(en <file.uue" "The \(en means use \fIstdin\fR"
.PP
\fIUud\fR decodes a file encoded with \fIuue\fR or
.UX
\fIuuencode\fR.
The decoded file is given the name that the original file had.  
The name information is part of the encoded file.
Mail headers and other junk before the encoded file are skipped.



